  "excerpt": "Or is it a distraction?",
  "image": "",
  "readTime": "1 min",
  "content": [
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Or is it a distraction?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Does strapping a supercomputer to you wrist make you more informed, or more effective at what you do? How about enabling notifications?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Or consider placing a hands-free AI-assisted speaker on your desk (or in your ears)—does it make you more productive?",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "Smart devices might be nice things to have, (and they often are). But we need to stop fooling ourselves by supposing they inherently make us any better off.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "That’s not to say we can’t leverage the tools we have to better ourselves. But leveraging a tool and being distracted by one are two entirely different things.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ]
    },
    {
      "_type": "block",
      "style": "normal",
      "children": [
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "It really comes down to intention and volume. It’s one thing to use a great",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "app",
          "marks": [
            "link-0"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "to guide your mindfulness practice. Or to jot down your thoughts. Or (even) to help you be",
          "marks": []
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": "less distracted",
          "marks": [
            "link-1"
          ]
        },
        {
          "_type": "span",
          "text": ". It’s entirely another, however, to use applications and devices to divert and occupy our attention every chance we get.",
          "marks": []
        }
      ],
